channel.title: 443 Interface Text Dump
channel.description:
I recently created a dump of all the 443 interfaces and their children that contain text and made it supply the IDs and 'config' values. Here's an example:
[code]Interface 261 27 = "%1%" Config 0: 11 0 Config 1: Config 2: Config 3: Config 4: Config 5:
36 = "Adjust Screen Brightness"
37 = "Adjust Music Volume"
38 = "Adjust Sound Effect Volume"
39 = "Adjust Area Sound Volume"
40 = "Run (on) Energy %1%" Config 0: 11 0 Config 1: Config 2: Config 3: Config 4: Config 5:
41 = "Chat Effects\n(currently on)"
42 = "Split Private Chat\n(currently on)"
43 = "Mouse buttons\n(currently 2)"
44 = "Accept Aid (currently on)"
45 = "House Options"
46 = "Run (off) Energy %1%" Config 0: 11 0 Config 1: Config 2: Config 3: Config 4: Config 5:
47 = "Chat Effects\n(currently off)"
48 = "Split Private Chat\n(currently off)"
49 = "Mouse buttons\n(currently 1)"
50 = "Accept Aid (currently off)"[/code]
[url=http://pastebin.com/SYfz96wn][b]View[/b][/url] or [url=http://www.mediafire.com/?fbs8ktctsufdo8d][b]Download[/b][/url]
~Lin
